Learning Objectives:
At the end of the course, your learning outcomes will include the development of:
1) Understanding of major leadership theories, styles and types of leaders, critical leadership attributes, and of leaders¿ relationships with their constituents;
2) Understanding of how leadership is important for lawyers and how leadership abilities influence and advance the work of lawyers; studying lawyers in leadership roles;
3) Development of personal leadership competencies such as effective team-building and teamwork, communication to inspire and persuade, collaboration in groups and mediation of problems and disputes, executive decision-making, cross-cultural competencies, and others;
4) Individual development of leadership path through design and implementation of plans for lifelong learning and lifelong leadership.
